TITLE:: OndaDef
summary:: Onda definition manager
categories:: UGens>Onda
related:: Classes/Onda

DESCRIPTION::
OndaDef manages compile and lifetime commands for link::Classes/Onda:: programs running on the SuperCollider server.

This first scaffold mirrors CmajorCollider workflow:

code::
OndaDef(\name, sourceOrPath).send;
::

Current host limits:

list::
## `ins`, `params`, and `events` must be scalar.
## `ins` and `params` must use `f32` endpoint types.
## `events` must use a single `f32` payload.
## `outs` must use `f32` endpoint types (`f32` or `f32[N]`).
## `buffers` must be `buffer[f32...]` and are driven from control-rate `bufnum` inputs.
::

CLASSMETHODS::

METHOD:: new
Create a new Onda definition.
ARGUMENT:: key
Unique link::Classes/Symbol:: for this definition.
ARGUMENT:: sources
Inline Onda source string, `.onda` file path string, or array mix of these.

METHOD:: free
Free a specific definition by key.

METHOD:: freeAll
Free all compiled OndaDefs and clear the global dictionary.

INSTANCEMETHODS::

METHOD:: send
Asynchronously compile on the server.
ARGUMENT:: server
Target link::Classes/Server::. Defaults to `Server.default`.
ARGUMENT:: action
Optional function evaluated after successful compile.
ARGUMENT:: numAllocate
Reserved for parity with CmajorCollider API.

METHOD:: add
Alias for `send`.

METHOD:: free
Unload this definition on the server.

METHOD:: query
Post cached input/output metadata.

METHOD:: ins
Parsed input metadata array.

METHOD:: outs
Flattened output channel count.

EXAMPLES::

code::
(
s.waitForBoot {
	var code = "
params:
  freq = 220 {20, 20000}

init:
  phase = 0.0

block:
  incr = freq / samplerate
  sample:
    out1 = sin(f32(twopi) * phase)
    phase = (phase + incr) % 1.0
";
	
    OndaDef(\sine, code).send;
	
	s.sync;
	
	{ Onda.ar(\sine, MouseX.kr(200, 1000, 1)).dup }.play;
};
)

::
